<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The function Zend_OpenId::normalize() removes URL Fragments. OpenID 2.0 uses them as Part of the OpenID to enable the "recycling" of OpenID URLs. This is an issue with Yahoo: <a href="http://developer.yahoo.com/openid/faq.html">http://developer.yahoo.com/openid/faq.html</a> (read "Identifier Recycling" on this page). I think normalize() should just keep the fragment.</p>

